{
  "stem": "23090.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So Auschwitz was not a, a, a-- it was never a good place to begin with-- but that, that was my introduction to the true world of what I call the-- away from the ghetto, which now I, as you call it, I compared to as paradise, to what was going-- to what was happening to me.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was, again, hungry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were, we were fed very, very little.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were just given like, a piece of dark bread in the morning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a water soup with the potato peelings for lunch.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, again, in the evening, it was like a potato-- there was water and a potato peeling in, in, in the evening.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that comprised the day of-- the full day of food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we just hungry, just hungry, and, and, just, and just beaten down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And just-- there, I was with people from every country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were with Hungarians, with Poles, with, with some from Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was a conglomeration of a lot of, a lot of Jews that were brought to Auschwitz and put together, but-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] That was to me, the worst camp.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was to me the worst camp on the conditions of being in a, what we call an exterminating camp, because that's, that, that was the only function that camp had.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Was not to keep you alive, or at least, if you survive it, then you survive it, and you go on, to the next phase, which I will tell you about.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But if you made it in Auschwitz, you're, you're kind of going to make it, unless there are other circumstances as you go on with, with this, with this journey.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But Auschwitz, to me, was the absolute nightmare.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
